main event: Two Nashville real estate salesmen observed several unidentified black, round objects hovering over Marrowbone Lake near Nashville, Tennessee on March 19, 1950.
interesting points: The objects were about the size of a 300 lb. bomb and made a noise like wind blowing through trees.
No motors were visible on the objects.
The objects were revolving at a speed of at least 500 miles per hour.
A spokesman at Stewart Air Force Base indicated the objects could not have been mistaken for military aircraft based on the witness descriptions.
The witnesses were contacted the next day, March 20, 1950, and had not yet investigated the incident further.
